This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with privacy-preserving distributed machine learning based on cryptography. It is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new method for logistic regression. Additionally, it may belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it deals with distributed machine learning. It may also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) as it involves secure computing. Finally, it may belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as logistic regression is commonly used in computer vision tasks.
